vc-layer-imagery/rectangle.description:
`optional` The rectangle of the layer. This rectangle can limit the visible portion of the imagery provider., default: `imageryProvider.rectangle`.

[Docs](https://zouyaoji.top/vue-cesium/#/en-US/component/vc-layer-imagery/#props)

vc-layer-imagery/alpha.description:
`optional` The alpha blending value of this layer, from 0.0 to 1.0., default: `1.0`.

[Docs](https://zouyaoji.top/vue-cesium/#/en-US/component/vc-layer-imagery/#props)

vc-layer-imagery/night-alpha.description:
`optional` The alpha blending value of this layer on the night side of the globe, from 0.0 to 1.0., default: `1.0`.

[Docs](https://zouyaoji.top/vue-cesium/#/en-US/component/vc-layer-imagery/#props)

vc-layer-imagery/day-alpha.description:
`optional` The alpha blending value of this layer on the day side of the globe, from 0.0 to 1.0., default: `1.0`.

[Docs](https://zouyaoji.top/vue-cesium/#/en-US/component/vc-layer-imagery/#props)

vc-layer-imagery/brightness.description:
`optional` The brightness of this layer. 1.0 uses the unmodified imagery color. Less than 1.0 makes the imagery darker while greater than 1.0 makes it brighter., default: `1.0`.

[Docs](https://zouyaoji.top/vue-cesium/#/en-US/component/vc-layer-imagery/#props)

vc-layer-imagery/contrast.description:
`optional` The contrast of this layer. 1.0 uses the unmodified imagery color. Less than 1.0 reduces the contrast while greater than 1.0 increases it., default: `1.0`.

[Docs](https://zouyaoji.top/vue-cesium/#/en-US/component/vc-layer-imagery/#props)

vc-layer-imagery/hue.description:
`optional` The hue of this layer. 0.0 uses the unmodified imagery color. This can either be a simple number or a function with the signature function(frameState, layer, x, y, level)., default: `0.0`.

[Docs](https://zouyaoji.top/vue-cesium/#/en-US/component/vc-layer-imagery/#props)

vc-layer-imagery/saturation.description:
`optional` The saturation of this layer. 1.0 uses the unmodified imagery color. Less than 1.0 reduces the saturation while greater than 1.0 increases it., default: `1.0`.

[Docs](https://zouyaoji.top/vue-cesium/#/en-US/component/vc-layer-imagery/#props)

vc-layer-imagery/gamma.description:
`optional`The gamma correction to apply to this layer. 1.0 uses the unmodified imagery color. This can either be a simple number or a function with the signature function(frameState, layer, x, y, level). The function is passed the current frame state, this layer, and the x, y, and level coordinates of the imagery tile for which the gamma is required, and it is expected to return the gamma value to use for the tile. The function is executed for every frame and for every tile, so it must be fast., default: `1.0`.

[Docs](https://zouyaoji.top/vue-cesium/#/en-US/component/vc-layer-imagery/#props)

vc-layer-imagery/split-direction.description:
`optional`The ImagerySplitDirection split to apply to this layer.  **LEFT: -1, NONE: 0, RIGHT: 1**, default: `0`.

[Docs](https://zouyaoji.top/vue-cesium/#/en-US/component/vc-layer-imagery/#props)

vc-layer-imagery/minification-filter.description:
`optional` The texture minification filter to apply to this layer. Possible values are TextureMinificationFilter.LINEAR and TextureMinificationFilter.NEAREST. **NEAREST: 9728, LINEAR: 9729, NEAREST_MIPMAP_NEAREST: 9984, LINEAR_MIPMAP_NEAREST: 9985, NEAREST_MIPMAP_LINEAR: 9986, NEAREST_MIPMAP_NEAREST: 9984**, default: `9729`.

[Docs](https://zouyaoji.top/vue-cesium/#/en-US/component/vc-layer-imagery/#props)

vc-layer-imagery/magnification-filter.description:
`optional` The texture minification filter to apply to this layer. Possible values are TextureMagnificationFilter.LINEAR and TextureMagnificationFilter.NEAREST. **NEAREST: 9728, LINEAR: 9729**, default: `9729`.

[Docs](https://zouyaoji.top/vue-cesium/#/en-US/component/vc-layer-imagery/#props)

vc-layer-imagery/show.description:
`optional` True if the layer is shown; otherwise, false., default: `true`.

[Docs](https://zouyaoji.top/vue-cesium/#/en-US/component/vc-layer-imagery/#props)

vc-layer-imagery/maximum-anisotropy.description:
`optional` The maximum anisotropy level to use for texture filtering. If this parameter is not specified, the maximum anisotropy supported by the WebGL stack will be used. Larger values make the imagery look better in horizon views., default: maximum supported.

[Docs](https://zouyaoji.top/vue-cesium/#/en-US/component/vc-layer-imagery/#props)

vc-layer-imagery/minimum-terrain-level.description:
`optional`The minimum terrain level-of-detail at which to show this imagery layer, or undefined to show it at all levels. Level zero is the least-detailed level.

[Docs](https://zouyaoji.top/vue-cesium/#/en-US/component/vc-layer-imagery/#props)

vc-layer-imagery/maximum-terrain-level.description:

vc-viewer/request-render-mode.description:
`optional` If true, rendering a frame will only occur when needed as determined by changes within the scene. Enabling reduces the CPU/GPU usage of your application and uses less battery on mobile, but requires using Scene#requestRender to render a new frame explicitly in this mode. This will be necessary in many cases after making changes to the scene in other parts of the API. See Improving Performance with Explicit Rendering., default: `false`.

[Docs](https://zouyaoji.top/vue-cesium/#/en-US/component/vc-viewer/#props)

vc-viewer/maximum-render-time-change.description:
`optional` If requestRenderMode is true, this value defines the maximum change in simulation time allowed before a render is requested. See Improving Performance with Explicit Rendering., default: `0.0`.

[Docs](https://zouyaoji.top/vue-cesium/#/en-US/component/vc-viewer/#props)

vc-post-process-stage/fragment-shader.description:
`required` The fragment shader to use. The default sampler2D uniforms are colorTexture and depthTexture. The color texture is the output of rendering the scene or the previous stage. The depth texture is the output from rendering the scene. The shader should contain one or both uniforms. There is also a vec2 varying named v_textureCoordinates that can be used to sample the textures.

[Docs](https://zouyaoji.top/vue-cesium/#/en-US/component/post-processes/vc-post-process-stage/#props)

vc-post-process-stage/uniforms.description:
`optional` An object whose properties will be used to set the shaders uniforms. The properties can be constant values or a function. A constant value can also be a URI, data URI, or HTML element to use as a texture.

[Docs](https://zouyaoji.top/vue-cesium/#/en-US/component/post-processes/vc-post-process-stage/#props)

vc-post-process-stage/texture-scale.description:
`optional` A number in the range (0.0, 1.0] used to scale the texture dimensions. A scale of 1.0 will render this post-process stage to a texture the size of the viewport., default: `1.0`.

[Docs](https://zouyaoji.top/vue-cesium/#/en-US/component/post-processes/vc-post-process-stage/#props)

vc-post-process-stage/force-power-of-two.description:
`optional` Whether or not to force the texture dimensions to be both equal powers of two. The power of two will be the next power of two of the minimum of the dimensions., default: `false`.

[Docs](https://zouyaoji.top/vue-cesium/#/en-US/component/post-processes/vc-post-process-stage/#props)

vc-primitive-tileset/maximum-memory-usag.description:

vc-primitive-tileset/cull-with-children-.description:

vc-primitive-tileset/cull-requests-while.description:
`optional` Optimization option. Don't request tiles that will likely be unused when they come back because of the camera's movement. This optimization only applies to stationary tilesets., default: `true`.

[Docs](https://zouyaoji.top/vue-cesium/#/en-US/component/primitives/vc-primitive-tileset/#props)

`optional` Optimization option. Multiplier used in culling requests while moving. Larger is more aggressive culling, smaller less aggressive culling., default: `60.0`.

vc-primitive-tileset/preload-flight-dest.description:
`optional` Optimization option. Preload tiles at the camera's flight destination while the camera is in flight., default: `true`.

[Docs](https://zouyaoji.top/vue-cesium/#/en-US/component/primitives/vc-primitive-tileset/#props)

vc-primitive-tileset/prefer-leaves.description:

vc-primitive-tileset/dynamic-screen-spac.description:

[Docs](https://zouyaoji.top/vue-cesium/#/en-US/component/primitives/vc-primitive-tileset/#props)

`optional` Density used to adjust the dynamic screen space error, similar to fog density., default: `0.00278`.

[Docs](https://zouyaoji.top/vue-cesium/#/en-US/component/primitives/vc-primitive-tileset/#props)

`optional` A factor used to increase the computed dynamic screen space error., default: `4.0`.

[Docs](https://zouyaoji.top/vue-cesium/#/en-US/component/primitives/vc-primitive-tileset/#props)

`optional` A ratio of the tileset's height at which the density starts to falloff., default: `0.25`.

[Docs](https://zouyaoji.top/vue-cesium/#/en-US/component/primitives/vc-primitive-tileset/#props)

vc-primitive-tileset/progressive-resolut.description:
`optional` Optimization option. If between (0.0, 0.5], tiles at or above the screen space error for the reduced screen resolution of progressiveResolutionHeightFraction*screenHeight will be prioritized first. This can help get a quick layer of tiles down while full resolution tiles continue to load., default: `0.3`.

[Docs](https://zouyaoji.top/vue-cesium/#/en-US/component/primitives/vc-primitive-tileset/#props)

vc-primitive-tileset/foveated-screen-spa.description:
`optional` Optimization option. Prioritize loading tiles in the center of the screen by temporarily raising the screen space error for tiles around the edge of the screen. Screen space error returns to normal once all the tiles in the center of the screen as determined by the Cesium3DTileset#foveatedConeSize are loaded., default: `true`.

[Docs](https://zouyaoji.top/vue-cesium/#/en-US/component/primitives/vc-primitive-tileset/#props)

vc-primitive-tileset/foveated-cone-size.description:
`optional` Optimization option. Used when Cesium3DTileset#foveatedScreenSpaceError is true to control the cone size that determines which tiles are deferred. Tiles that are inside this cone are loaded immediately. Tiles outside the cone are potentially deferred based on how far outside the cone they are and their screen space error. This is controlled by Cesium3DTileset#foveatedInterpolationCallback and Cesium3DTileset#foveatedMinimumScreenSpaceErrorRelaxation. Setting this to 0.0 means the cone will be the line formed by the camera position and its view direction. Setting this to 1.0 means the cone encompasses the entire field of view of the camera, disabling the effect., default: `0.1`.

[Docs](https://zouyaoji.top/vue-cesium/#/en-US/component/primitives/vc-primitive-tileset/#props)

vc-primitive-tileset/foveated-minimum-sc.description:
`optional` Optimization option. Used when Cesium3DTileset#foveatedScreenSpaceError is true to control the starting screen space error relaxation for tiles outside the foveated cone. The screen space error will be raised starting with tileset value up to Cesium3DTileset#maximumScreenSpaceError based on the provided Cesium3DTileset#foveatedInterpolationCallback., default: `0.0`.

[Docs](https://zouyaoji.top/vue-cesium/#/en-US/component/primitives/vc-primitive-tileset/#props)

vc-primitive-tileset/foveated-interpolat.description:
`optional` Optimization option. Used when Cesium3DTileset#foveatedScreenSpaceError is true to control how much to raise the screen space error for tiles outside the foveated cone, interpolating between Cesium3DTileset#foveatedMinimumScreenSpaceErrorRelaxation and Cesium3DTileset#maximumScreenSpaceError

[Docs](https://zouyaoji.top/vue-cesium/#/en-US/component/primitives/vc-primitive-tileset/#props)

vc-primitive-tileset/foveated-time-delay.description:
`optional` Optimization option. Used when Cesium3DTileset#foveatedScreenSpaceError is true to control how long in seconds to wait after the camera stops moving before deferred tiles start loading in. This time delay prevents requesting tiles around the edges of the screen when the camera is moving. Setting this to 0.0 will immediately request all tiles in any given view., default: `0.2`.

[Docs](https://zouyaoji.top/vue-cesium/#/en-US/component/primitives/vc-primitive-tileset/#props)

vc-primitive-tileset/skip-level-of-detai.description:

[Docs](https://zouyaoji.top/vue-cesium/#/en-US/component/primitives/vc-primitive-tileset/#props)

vc-primitive-tileset/base-screen-space-e.description:

[Docs](https://zouyaoji.top/vue-cesium/#/en-US/component/primitives/vc-primitive-tileset/#props)

vc-primitive-tileset/skip-screen-space-e.description:

[Docs](https://zouyaoji.top/vue-cesium/#/en-US/component/primitives/vc-primitive-tileset/#props)

vc-primitive-tileset/skip-levels.description:

[Docs](https://zouyaoji.top/vue-cesium/#/en-US/component/primitives/vc-primitive-tileset/#props)

vc-primitive-tileset/immediately-load-de.description:
`optional` When skipLevelOfDetail is true, only tiles that meet the maximum screen space error will ever be downloaded. Skipping factors are ignored and just the desired tiles are loaded., default: false.

[Docs](https://zouyaoji.top/vue-cesium/#/en-US/component/primitives/vc-primitive-tileset/#props)

When this property is false, memory usage and texture upload time are potentially reduced., default: `true`.

If false, UrlTemplateImageryProvider#pickFeatures will immediately return undefined (indicating no pickable features) without communicating with the server. Set this property to false if you know your data source does not support picking features or if you don't want this provider's features to be pickable. Note that this can be dynamically overridden by modifying the UriTemplateImageryProvider#enablePickFeatures property., default: `true`.
